#
# Status of P/S on various platforms
#

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
General notes
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Player is developed on Linux x86 and OS X.3. Status of other platforms
is tested infrequently and may be out of date. If you have information
about other platforms, please contact the Player lead maintainer,
Brian Gerkey <gerkey@users.sourceforge.net>


# Y = YES
# N = NO
# U = UNTESTED

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Machine       |   OS               |  Clients?  | Hardware?  |  Stage? |  RTKGUI? 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
x86            Linux 2.2, 2.4, 2.6      Y           Y           Y           Y
Sparc          SunOS 5.6, 5.8           Y           U           Y           Y
Sparc64        Linux 2.4                Y           U           Y           U
SA1110 (Bitsy) Linux 2.4.19	        U           Y           N           N
SA1110 (iPAQ)  Linux 2.4.??             Y           Y           N           N
Alpha          Linux 2.2                Y           U           Y           U
x86            FreeBSD 4.7              Y           U           Y           Y
PowerPC        OS X.2, X.3              Y           U           Y           Y
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Platform Notes
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Sparc/SunOS:
   - udpbroadcast driver causes Player to hang.

x86/FreeBSD:
   - udpbroadcast driver causes Player to hang.

Alpha/Linux:
   - Stage lbddevice segfaults in an STL list iteration.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
